snippet.textDisplay: Why are your inches so small? I can’t follow this...              On a more serious note anyone wearing gloves around any sort of spinning or rotating tool or blade makes me very uneasy. I work in industry and many times I’ve seen people who are afraid to get dirty or hurt their hand get seriously injured when part of the glove catches a rotating tool or blade and yank their hand into it. The worst was a young guy had gloves on running the mill and he brushed the chips away with his finger. The glove finger tip caught the spinning end mill and the glove finger spun and twisted his finger right off right were it attached to his hand. It happened in less than a second. He didn’t even feel it. It happened in less than a blink. He saw his finger laying there and went into shock and passed out. Be careful and keep building.👍🏻

snippet.textDisplay: I've worked in the timber industry for over 45 years. What you are doing is an absolute NO NO. You never ever work with gloves on whilst working with Electric Saws. If the blade even clips the glove slightly it will pull your hand into the blade and it could be good by to your hand. I've seen many many hands fingers and other injuries due to people wearing Gloves around saws. And that includes Chainsaws.
